Comment.MultiLanguageText: Selection of brake 1 or 2 - set to 0 for brake 1, set to 1for brake 2.
Direction of rotation - set to 0 for positive, set to 1 fornegative.
Torque 1 or 2 - set to 0 for Test torquefactor 1, set to 1for Test torquefactor 2.
Brake closed - Set to 1 to confirm that the brake isclosed (External brakes only)
Brake test is active - 1 = brake test active.
Brake test ok - 1 = brake test was successful.
Brake test nok - 1 = brake test was NOT successful.
Close brake request for external brakes
Load torque sign - direction of the load torque,0 = positive, 1 = negative. Can be used to determinethe SBT direction.
